Posted Friday, 2025-02-07.
’Ů@0711f356a2c7088dc046152c2540aac097e7c2f6ca9eb4b76e83024c9fee9883ÚyTitle: title: 'This week in Nushell #285'
Path: Highlights
Content:
Since this was a release-week, a number of the changes below are included in the 
[link: /blog/2025-02-04-nushell_0_102_0.html] 0.102.0 release
, a few were housekeeping tasks related

to the release, and some items will, of course, appear in nightly builds and 
``main``
 (and eventually 0.103).
A belated thanks to 
[link: https://github.com/0x4D5352] @0x4D5352
 for bringing much-needed consistency to the documentation. With output now commented out in code blocks, you can copy examples directly from the docs and paste them into Nushell.
In case you missed it, in December 
[link: https://github.com/ayax79] @ayax79
 added 
``polars open``
 support for Amazon S3 in

[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14648] #14648
 and followed up this week with 
``polars save``
 to S3 in 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15005] #15005
!
And 
[link: https://github.com/WindSoilder] WindSoilder
 made it easier to debug Nushell errors with a new backtrace feature (
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/14945] #14945
).
Other changes by repository:
